          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Be Warned: This School Prioritizes Social-Media Campaign Over Your Child's Education\n\nThe Academy School is the epitome of empty promises and exorbitant costs.  They drown potential parents in a sea of slick marketing, yet the actual education is a mediocre swamp.\n\nHere's the truth behind the dazzling facade:\n\nSubpar Academics: Don't be fooled! The academics are just average. Not worth paying a penny more than other schools.\n\nHighway Robbery Fees: The fees are an outrageous scam. They shamelessly charge illogical charges that go straight to funding their self-serving PR campaigns and fill owner's coffer. This school sells everything from uniform to even the pencils and charge a fortune that you are arm-twisted to pay.\n\nTeacher Revolving Doors: The school exploits its teachers with pitiful salaries. This unsurprisingly leads to a constant stream of resignations, leaving your child with a disrupted and fractured learning experience. Frequent new faces don't allow for the development of strong foundations or meaningful relationships with educators. This is a recipe for educational disaster!\n\nMalacious propaganda : Look at the number of 5 star ratings by students of the school. Ever heard of students being indicated to post ratings or face consequences. Well ! Nothing directly instructed to them, but the numerous positive posts from students must make you think.\n\nDon't be a victim!  If you care about your child's education and getting your money's worth, RUN, don't just walk away from TAS.  They prioritize image over substance and are happy to leave your child's education floundering.  Look elsewhere for a school that truly invests in its teachers and prioritizes quality academics.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
